reviewText: One great thing about this specialization (now halfway through) is that the instructor is clearly a great educator, both intelligent on the subject matter and enthusiastic about sharing knowledge and his experience.  The only time the wind was taken out of my sails while learning this material was the final peer-reviewed assignment was inconsistently nit-picked compared to quizzes in the modules.  This cannot take away from the enjoyment I had learning these skills in the previous 99% of the course (part 3).

It is a good course for students who want to start their careers in the field of consulting.  The course gives you an idea about how consultants work in the marketplace and how they approach towards any problem statement.
another helpful module, thank you very much; happy to start with module 4 soon
G​reat course, for both seasoned and new consultants. Keep the good work!
A​s a "red airplane" :) it is perfect to see how to get the benefit from the experiences that we had after many years. Clear messages for all kind of audiences, it was really nice to have.
